fdie in an undisclosed role, and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/eminem">Eminem</a> in a cameo appearance.</p><p> The first film has a large fanbase, and as such the arrival of the sequel&#39;s trailer has been met with enthusiasm on X (formerly Twitter). “Yes!!!! Best news of the week, year, maybe decade?!?!” said one, with another asserting: “Adam knows what his fans want”.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">是的！！！！ Best news of the week, year, maybe decade?!?! <a href="https://t.co/wtPqBMbZPu">https://t.co/wtPqBMbZPu</a></p><p> — Marshall Kelner (@MarshallKelner) <a href="https://twitter.com/MarshallKelner/status/1901978450300187003?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 18, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Adam knows what his fans want. <a href="https://t.co/BXdrzo9eoi">https://t.co/BXdrzo9eoi</a></p><p> — Oh Danny <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f365.png" alt="🍥" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> (@DanC88888) <a href="https://twitter.com/DanC88888/status/1901986301370302694?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 18, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Some hold the first movie in such high esteem that they are cautious about a follow up. “ <em>Happy Gilmore</em> is my &#39;happy place&#39;, pls be good” said one, with another adding: “Most sequels aren&#39;t as good as the first movie … but I don&#39;t f$#%ing care! I&#39;m all in for this!”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Happy Gilmore is my &quot;happy place.&quot; pls be good <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f64f.png" alt="🙏" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em